    <section title="Introduction">
      <t>
This document proposes a control bit in IPv6 RA PIO message called the X bit,
that indicates that the host receiving this RA is the only host in the prefix.
The host then can stop using ND and DAD for addresses within this prefix.
      </t>
      <t>
